        <img src="../../assets/statiuniti-bosniaerzegovina-worldcup2026.py" class="cover-hero" alt="Exclusive preview of USA vs Bosnia & Herzegovina at MetLife Stadium. Tactical analysis, pre-match atmosphere, and predicted lineups for July 2, 2026.">
        <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #666; font-style: italic; margin-top: -8px; margin-bottom: 20px;">The majestic MetLife Stadium in New York/New Jersey, ready to host the epic showdown.</p>

        <div class="content">
            <p>The electric air of New York and the imposing presence of <strong>MetLife Stadium</strong> set the stage for a night destined for the history books. On <strong>July 2, 2026, at 02:00 CEST</strong>, the floodlights will shine on a captivating encounter: the <strong>United States</strong> face <strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina</strong> in a clash of destinies, dreams, and contrasting football philosophies. The atmosphere ahead of kickoff is charged with a feverish anticipation that only grand occasions can evoke, with American fans eager to propel their heroes toward a legendary milestone.</p><h3>The Star-Spangled Surge and the Quest for Glory</h3><p>Under the strategic stewardship of <strong>Mauricio Pochettino</strong>, the USMNT enters this fixture determined to dictate a relentless tempo. The transition speed and creative flair of stars like <strong>Christian Pulisic</strong> serve as the sharpest weapons for a side eager to prove its maturity on the global stage. It is not merely about securing a victory, but sending a statement of authority, capitalizing on the home-field advantage in a stadium expected to boil over with patriotic fervor.</p><h3>Barbarez's Steel Trap and the Dragon's Pride</h3><p>On the opposing side, Bosnia and Herzegovina counters with their trademark tactical discipline and ironclad resolve. Head coach <strong>Sergej Barbarez</strong> has forged a resilient unit, capable of absorbing pressure and striking ruthlessly when opportunity knocks. The enduring leadership of <strong>Edin Džeko</strong> and the physical dominance of a defense anchored by <strong>Sead Kolašinac</strong> will be the cornerstones of their defensive wall. The "Dragons" know they are the underdogs, but it is precisely under such high-stakes pressure that their warrior spirit shines brightest.</p><h3>Tactical Chess: The Battleground in Midfield</h3><p>The outcome of this duel will likely be decided in the engine room. The sheer dynamism of the American midfield, marshaled by <strong>Weston McKennie</strong>, will attempt to dismantle the compact, low-block defensive lines drawn up by Barbarez. It promises to be a battle of nerves and spatial precision, where a single positional lapse could prove fatal. Quick transitions will be crucial for the hosts, whereas the Bosnians will rely on structured possession and lethal vertical counter-attacks.</p><h3>The Probable Lineups on the MetLife Turf</h3><div class="lineups"><p><strong>United States (4-3-3):</strong> Turner; Scally, Richards, Ream, Robinson; McKennie, Musah, Reyna; Weah, Balogun, Pulisic.</p><p class="coach"><em>Ct:</em> Mauricio Pochettino</p><br><p><strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina (5-3-2):</strong> Vasilj; Gazibegović, Katić, Bičakčić, Kolašinac, Dedić; Hajradinović, Tahirović, Šarić; Demirović, Džeko.</p><p class="coach"><em>Ct:</em> Sergej Barbarez</p></div>
